=head1 DESCRIPTION

Determines whether CloudFront includes the C<X-Frame-Options> HTTP
response header and the header's value.

For more information about the C<X-Frame-Options> HTTP response header,
see X-Frame-Options
(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Frame-Options)
in the MDN Web Docs.

=head1 ATTRIBUTES


=head2 B<REQUIRED> FrameOption => Str

The value of the C<X-Frame-Options> HTTP response header. Valid values
are C<DENY> and C<SAMEORIGIN>.

For more information about these values, see X-Frame-Options
(https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTTP/Headers/X-Frame-Options)
in the MDN Web Docs.


=head2 B<REQUIRED> Override => Bool

A Boolean that determines whether CloudFront overrides the
C<X-Frame-Options> HTTP response header received from the origin with
the one specified in this response headers policy.



